      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Creating Access to Rehabilitation for Every Senior (CARES) Act of 2015</b></p> <p>Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act with respect to coverage of extended care services without regard to the three-day prior hospitalization requirement (non-post-hospital extended care services).</p> <p>Restricts such coverage to non-post-hospital extended care services in a qualified skilled nursing facility.</p> <p>Directs the Medicare Payment Advisory Commission (MEDPAC) to study the cost of impact of this Act.</p>]]></text>
